    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A strata of limestone chalk formed from shell deposited in the Middle Triassic formation. Found in Europe, most commonly in Germany, lying above the Bunter and and below the Keuper layers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
